    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1: SRPX2 overexpression in cultured cortical neurons increased excitatory, but not inhibitory, synapse density.\n\nFigure 2: SRPX2 knockdown and secretion of dominant negative SRPX2 decrease excitatory synaptic density in cultured cortical neurons.\n\nFigure 4: In vivo assay. \"Neurons transfected with SRXP2-directed shRNA showed a decrease in the density of dendritic spines on the apical dendrite of layer V/VI neurons (Fig. 4, B and C), an effect that is reversed by cotransfection of the shRNA-resistant SRPX2 construct.\". Experimental description: Results, Figure 2 legend: \"Rat cortical neurons were cotransfected with BFP and scrambled shRNA, SRPX2 shRNA, or SRPX2 shRNA and rescue construct (SRPX2 rescue) and then stained for excitatory or inhibitory synaptic markers.\"",
